detaileddescription.para:
To read any Nuball2-like TTree :    // Loads the TTree or TChain ...
   Event event;
   event.reading(ttree);
 If you are only interested in a few branches, you can choose them by adding an option :    event.reading(ttree, "lst"); // Reads only the multiplicity, label, timestamp and relatative time.
 Note the multiplicity will always be activated, because it is mandatory to read the root file.

You can add Hits to an event using the Event::push_back or Event::push_front methods :    event.push_back(hit);

   event.push_front(hit);
 When the event is complete (e.g. in an event builder), you can for instance write it down or analyse it, then call Event::clear() to empty it.
